SUMMARY
=======

This script will parse a list of pins to be monitored from /etc/mqtt-gpio-trigger/ and publish MQTT message whenever they change state. This particular incantation of it uses the WiringPi library from https://projects.drogon.net/raspberry-pi/wiringpi/ to monitor inputs on a Raspberry Pi.

WARNING
=======
As above, it uses the WiringPi library, especially the gpio command. Next version will use exported GPIO pins and be platform agnostic (theoretically)

INSTALL
=======

mkdir /usr/local/mqtt-gpio-trigger/ /etc/mqtt-gpio-trigger/
cd /usr/local/
git clone git://github.com/kylegordon/mqtt-gpio-trigger.git
cp mqtt-gpio-trigger.cfg.example /etc/mqtt-gpio-trigger/mqtt-gpio-trigger.cfg
cp mqtt-gpio-trigger.init /etc/init.d/mqtt-gpio-trigger
update-rc.d mqtt-gpio-trigger defaults
cp mqtt-gpio-trigger.default /etc/default/mqtt-gpio-trigger
/etc/init.d/mqtt-gpio-trigger start
